Paladin of the 50th shield<BR>
<a href="http://www.emeraldis.com/~booraembj/">Exiles</a>, Xegony<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utigerheart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tigerheart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 229<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/8/02 9:38:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=959.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Suggested focus effect / item</span><hr size=1> If you can afford to make a RO BP, you should try  to buy a Crusty BP. Crusty BP has  better stats than RO.<br>
<br>
RO armor nowdays isnt worth questing at all. they should make it used in a quest so pallys would actually do the quests , like the SK Darkforge armors is needed for SK epic.<br>
<br>
Crusty armors is as cheap as Ro and much better stats in most the pieces.<br>
<br>
As the fact in raising your DD output. there is the AA route you can go. Spell casting fury will effect DM and IoN, and any Proc DD weapon, like Ghoulbane.  It will raise the dmg of the spells by 30% when it goes off, which is seldom at lvl 1, but it increses as you pour more points into it. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=152485">Tigerheart</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujarrex.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jarrex</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/9/02 9:12:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=959.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Suggested focus effect / item</span><hr size=1> I think that the best way to &quot;fix&quot; old world armors is to drop the gems. Unnecessary and in my opinion, the only reason not to do the quests. <br>
<br>
But I agree, the ro bp should be more than 2str better than neth chitin. I got a neth chitin in less than 10 minutes, soloing, at level 45. Got some piercing weapon as well. It would have taken me much longer, more money,and a lot more risk to do the ro quest. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uangelsyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Angelsyn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.aol.com/tdlutenatenjou/icon_keyne.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blessed Protector</span><br>  Posts: 487<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/9/02 1:50:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=959.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/tdlutenatenjou/icon_keyne.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Suggested focus effect / item</span><hr size=1> I agree that the Ro Armour should be used in some Quest later on...  Someone suggested it being used to get the Wind-Etched Armour of Ro from PoA, which would be a great idea IMHO.<br>
